[src:generating-functions-deep/formal-power-series] One can perform algebraic operations on power series to generate new power series.
[src:generating-functions-deep/formal-power-series] In the case of formal power series with complex coefficients, its complex powers are well defined for series *f* with constant term equal to 1.
[src:generating-functions-deep/formal-power-series] The exponent rules $(f^{\alpha })^{\beta }=f^{\alpha \beta }$ and $f^{\alpha }g^{\alpha }=(fg)^{\alpha }$ easily follow for formal power series *f*, *g*.
