[src:generating-functions-deep/generating-function-p01] Polynomials are a special case of ordinary generating functions, corresponding to finite sequences, or equivalently sequences that vanish after a certain point.
[src:generating-functions-deep/generating-function-p01] These are important in that many finite sequences can usefully be interpreted as generating functions, such as the Poincaré polynomial and others.
