[src:generating-functions-deep/symbolic-method-combinatorics] Typically, one starts with the *neutral class* ${\mathcal {E}}$ , containing a single object of size 0 (the *neutral object*, often denoted by $\epsilon$ ), and one or more *atomic classes* ${\mathcal {Z}}$ , each containing a single object of size 1.
