[src:generating-functions-deep/symbolic-method-combinatorics] The elegance of symbolic combinatorics lies in that the set theoretic, or *symbolic*, relations translate directly into *algebraic* relations involving the generating functions.
[src:generating-functions-deep/symbolic-method-combinatorics] In this article, we will follow the convention of using script uppercase letters to denote combinatorial classes and the corresponding plain letters for the generating functions (so the class ${\mathcal {A}}$ has generating function $A(z)$ ).
[src:generating-functions-deep/symbolic-method-combinatorics] There are two types of generating functions commonly used in symbolic combinatorics—ordinary generating functions, used for combinatorial classes of unlabelled objects, and exponential generating functions, used for classes of labelled objects.
